nce you kill one, killing it again isn't a new experience. sitting in the same dungeon time and time again, that is not a new place more than once.<br><br>so what do we play for? why do some of us level our characters to the mid-50's? who would sit through any 50+ level &quot;for fun&quot;? are we insane?<br><br>No. There is one reason we play for, whether we admit it or not.<br><br>We play for loot.<br><br>There is no sensible reason to go to NToV time and time again, except for loot. who likes dying? not me. there aren't many people who have never died on a raid; in fact, I have yet to meet someone who has not died in a plane, camp, or dungeon, save someone who has not made the levels for such. It is just as hard to find someone who has not died multiple times on a single raid; sure, it may have been a while since they did, but I'm certain that every one of us over 46 has been &quot;pwned&quot; in the plane of fear, even if it was back when anyone could go in. You can't tell me that this was done because of an adventurous spirit; no, we wanted to see what kinds of goodies we could pull out of there. Certainly, if the place is that dangerous, there must be something worth having.<br><br>Now, let's dispense with the BS and play this game the way it was intended to be played. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uquttepie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutte Pie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 5:21:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2141.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.synmicro.com/prod/itempics/parentaladvisory.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left c