s/clubs/concerts, forgot what it was like to run, play sports, mountain bike, climb, rappel, hike, go camping, fish, target shoot (HK .45...love it!), drink some beers, smoke cigars, etc etc and MOST IMPORTANTLY GET LAID!<br><br>Life was rough, and all I had was my EQ addiction =(<br><br><br>My second go at EQ is MUCH much less intense, more centered on playing to have fun and if im not having fun I dont play. I had good gear with Belegir before I relinquished him so I am not very motivated to get the &quot;ph4t l00t&quot; now, because I know what it feels like to have epics, good armor, etc etc. I also have fully resumed things I used to do in RL; the stuff I mentioned above. Thus I dont have as much time or want to spend as much time playing EQ anymore.<br><br>I'm fully convinced that if you play EQ for gear you will always be chasing the white elephant. Never fully happy. You will quit frustrated, or simply get bored.  I also think after looking back on it all that having an active and fun real life IS NOT compatible with putting in the level of committment it takes to get to the higher end of EQ. Some of you who are playing the high end game may not have been that active before EQ, and this is a more normal RL routine for you. Great. But I can atest that if you go to grad school full time, work 20 hours per week, and work out 5 days a week you DO NOT have time for EQ. You will be a very casual player at best, and you just may want to spend some of your free time NOT sitting in front of the computer chasing and killing pixels.<br><br>So play the game for fun, dont kill your real life for it....and realize that if you make the committment neccesary for games like EQ you will have to pay the piper at some point. My advice is do what you have to, but if you are playing for loot you will never win. Play for friends, enjoy &quot;today&quot; when you are playing, because at some point it will all go away.<br><br><br>I havent been on in about 3 weeks, and honestly I havent missed it at all.<br><br><br><br><br> <p><b>Elrenn Longstrider</b><br>Ranger of Surefall Glade<br><br><i>Tolan's last student</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/unumenorean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numenorean</A> at: 2/6/02 7:21:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=simplee>Simplee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 7:25:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2141.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why do we play this game?</span><hr size=1> Nope, changed my mind about my post. The post before me summed it up much better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'm here for the fun, but not to let all other fun fall to the wayside.<br><br><br>Simplee<br>Torvus'Vir <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=simplee>Simplee</A> at: 2/6/02 7:29:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usomberlainwayfaerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Somberlain Wayfaerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 7:27:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2141.topic&index=13>Reply</a> 