I've considered leaving more than once, but there are gnomish pirates and wood elf vixens who I would miss too much.  Seeing my good friend Ellixia leave the game a few months ago made me realize that friends in EQ are no different than any other friends in life, whether your conversations are over lunch or over the Internet, if you really get to know them.  <br><br>Loot be damned.  The images in your mind might only be of pixels, but when you log out for the last time, you'll realize that the text scrolled by way too fast.<br><br><br> <p>Somberlain Wayfaerer<BR>Wanderer of Druzzil Ro<BR>Guild Leader of the Justice Knights<BR><a href="http://www.geocities.com/justiceknights/jk.html">www.geocities.com/justiceknights</a> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ualihjazanzibar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alihja Zanzibar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Alihjadomis</span><br>  Posts: 1007<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/6/02 7:42:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846generaldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2141.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.rutabaga-paradox.org/images/mullet.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why do we play this game?</span><hr size=1> I play this game to have a social interation with the other humans who play it.  The loot I get doesn't matter, as long as I have fun in the WAY I get it.<br><br>I do it all for the smacktalk...<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.rutabaga-paradox.org/smacktalk/snugglie/collage.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br><br>I don't get people's infatuation with equipment..  they run up and right click on you, and stare at your stuff.  Loot hungry heathens!  Some people judge you for the crap you wear..  it's such a shallow society that we play in today.  The whol